quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  46,21,"Remember, too, the brother of Ad when he warned his people in AL AHKAF - and before and since his time there have been warners - \"Worship none but God: verily I fear for you the punishment of the great day"
  46,22,"They said, \"Art thou come to us to turn us away from our gods? Bring on us now the woes which thou threatenest if thou speakest truth"
  46,23,"That knowledge,\" said he, \"is with God alone: I only proclaim to you the message with which I am sent. But I perceive that ye are a people sunk in ignorance"
  46,24,"So when they saw a cloud coming straight for their valleys, they said, \"It is a passing cloud that shall give us rain.\" \"Nay, it is that whose speedy coming ye challenged a blast wherein is an afflictive punishment"
  46,25,"It will destroy everything at the bidding of its Lord!\" And at morn nought was to be seen but their empty dwellings! Thus repay we a wicked people"
  46,26,"With power had we endued them, even as with power have we endued you; and we had given them ears and eyes and hearts: yet neither their eyes, nor their ears, nor their hearts aided them at all, when once they gainsaid the signs of God; but that punishment which they had mocked at enveloped them on all sides"
  46,27,"Of old, too, did we destroy the cities which were round about you; and, in order that they might return to us, we varied our signs before them"
  46,28,"But did those whom they took for gods beside God as his kindred deities, help them? Nay, they withdrew from them. Such was their delusion, and their device"